			<abstract>
				<p>Report by the couple Rosa and Koppel Friedfertig from Hamburg about their experiences during the “Polenaktion” in 1938, the forced
					eviction of Jews with Polish citizenship from Germany to Poland, with a description of the living conditions in the village and
					reception camp Zbaszyn and their escape to Palestine.</p>
