	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-YV5245989_01.jpg"/>
			<p>- 1 -</p>

			<p><term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_polenaktion">Poland - Action</term>
				<date when="1938">1938</date>. - In the camp <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3080495/zbaszyn.html">Sbonczyn</placeName><note
					place="bottom">handwritten addition</note></p>
			<p>Report of the couple Mrs. <persName ref="#ehri_et_friedfertig_rosa">Rosa Friedfertig</persName> and Mr. <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_friedfertig_koppel">Koppel Friedfertig</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911298/hamburg.html"
					>Hamburg</placeName>. <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/293397/tel-aviv.html">Tel Aviv</placeName>, Feierbergstr. 16</p>
			<p>Stenographical record by <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000453">Dr. K. Ball</persName>, early
					<date when="1944-11">November 1944</date>.</p>

			<p>1.) We were <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1149" type="subject">citizens</term> and lived in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911298/hamburg.html">Hamburg</placeName>-<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911296/altona.html">Altona</placeName> for over 30 years. Our eldest <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> studied in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2925533/frankfurt-am-main.html">Frankfurt</placeName> and already had a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-867" type="subject">student certificate</term> for <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6254930/palestine.html">Palestine</placeName>. Her papers were in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2925533/frankfurt-am-main.html">Frankfurt</placeName>, she herself was just with us to say goodbye.
				Our second <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> was in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName> on <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-913" type="subject">Hachscharah</term>, the third went to school. We lived
				in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911296/altona.html">Altona</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911296/altona.html">Adolfstr. 164</placeName>. Our eldest <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> temporarily helped out as a guide in
				the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911296/altona.html">Wilhelmshöhe</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-913" type="subject">preparation camp</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2948066/blankenese.html">Blankenese</placeName>. In this <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567">camp</term> the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> boys were picked up on <date when="1938-10-28"
					>October 28, 1938</date>. Our <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term>
				came home in the afternoon instead of in the evening, was very excited, but told us nothing.</p>

			<p>2.) In the night from <date when="1938-10-28">28</date> to <date when="1938-10-29">29 October</date> between 5 and ½ 6, still in full
				darkness, I heard footsteps in the hallway, then it rang and 2 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120"
					type="subject">police officers</term> demanded entrance. They came with the order to pick us all up and called all by name. I said
				that the oldest <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> was in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2925533/frankfurt-am-main.html">Frankfurt</placeName> and the second in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>. In the end, however, they only demanded that my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term> come with me. They also said that he
				should <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">dress</term> warmly, have <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">breakfast</term> and be allowed 10 Marks. They took
				their time to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">dress</term> in peace, to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-737" type="subject">pray</term>, and came back after 10 minutes. They took
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1141" type="subject">passport</term>, but they should have taken me
				with them, too, but they wanted to refrain from doing so. Then my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
					type="subject">husband</term> was picked up and taken to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1166"
					type="subject">police headquarters</term>. We had asked what would happen to those <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject">officials</term> said we didn’t need to get upset, it
				wasn’t something that affected my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term>
				personally, but a general action against the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1149" type="subject">Polish
					citizens</term>. At first he would come to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1166" type="subject"
					>police headquarters</term>, which would go on if they themselves did not know.</p>

			<p>3.) Afterwards I brought my youngest <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term>
				to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214" type="subject">school</term>. When I came onto the street, a
				horrible picture appeared: everywhere <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-428">policemen</orgName> who
				led <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> of all ages and sex away. They even
				went into the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue</term> and got the people
				out. Then I went to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">congregation</term>, where
				mainly <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> flocked together, as well as <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1217" type="subject">stateless</term> men who had not been picked up. In
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">congregation</term> we were told that they were
				in negotiations with the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1118" type="subject">consulates</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911298/hamburg.html">Hamburg</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>, that we had to wait, that they could not say anything at the
				moment. From there I went to pick up my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
					>daughter</term> from <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214" type="subject">school</term> and had the
				big <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> try to call the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>, so that she would come to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911296/altona.html">Hamburg-Altona</placeName> immediately and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> would be together. Then I went to visit
				my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term>. I found him in a huge gymnasium
				where hundreds of people had already gathered, old people, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826"
					type="subject">men</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">babies</term> in prams, etc., etc. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">congregation</term> had some representatives there,
				they had sent food and took orders from the individuals, which perhaps could still be done. Miss <persName ref="#ehri_et_ellern"
					>Ellern</persName>, who is now here in the country (note by <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000453">Dr. Ball</persName>: working as a social worker in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/295514/bnei-brak.html">Bnei Brak</placeName>), worked there alongside various board members of the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">congregation</term>. After I had spoken to my
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term> and wanted to leave again, the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject">guard</term> did not let me through. I said I
				was not <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> at all, but only visited my
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term>. He replied that he didn’t think
				so, but if I hadn’t been picked up, it had only happened by mistake, now I had to</p>
			<p>I'll stay here. I was very desperate because my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject"
					>children</term> did not know where I was, I turned to Miss <persName ref="#ehri_et_ellern">Ellern</persName>. She went straight
				to the door with me and said to me in a loud voice: <q>Sheep, I told you to bring my files, they are in my desk in the study</q>. Then
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject">guard</term> let me pass.</p>

			<p>4.) At home I cooked <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">lunch</term>. There it knocked
				again and there appeared again</p>

			<pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-YV5245989_02.jpg"/>
			<p>- 2 -</p>

			<p>two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject">policemen</term>, this time to pick up me and
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">kids</term>. I concealed that my eldest <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> was in the apartment, and went with
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">little one</term> together. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject">officer</term> said I could take anything I could
				carry, and I packed as many suitcases as I had, far too many of course. But then the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject">officer</term> let me go down the stairs several
				times with the suitcases, so that I could take them all. Downstairs, the Green Car was waiting, and we got up and were, too, were
				brought to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1166" type="subject">police headquarters</term> and to
				the hall I already knew.</p>

			<p>5.) From there we were taken by lorry to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911295/bahnhof-hamburg-altona.html">Altona
					station</placeName> and to a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">train</term>
				waiting there. It was a real passenger <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">train</term>,
				heated and illuminated. On the platform stood big tables and there were representatives of the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004665">Hamburg</orgName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911296/altona.html">Altona</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">congregation</term>, on the tables <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> packages etc., which were given along,
				also money. In the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">train</term> were of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> of all ages, often still with <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-737" type="subject">prayer shawls</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-737" type="subject">prayer books</term>, since it was just Friday evening.
				At the last moment my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> came from
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>, who had just left and was informed at home by
				some neighbours. In the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1166" type="subject">police headquarters</term>
				she was told that she didn’t<note place="bottom">handwritten addition</note> have to join us, but she wanted to be with us and just
				reached the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">train</term>. My other <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> stayed in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911298/hamburg.html">Hamburg</placeName> because she already had the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-867" type="subject">certificate</term>. That same evening she flew to
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2925533/frankfurt-am-main.html">Frankfurt</placeName> and was able to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-880" type="subject">emigrate</term> immediately to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6254930/palestine.html">Palestine</placeName>.</p>

			<p>6.) The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">train</term> left at about ½ 8 o'clock in the
				evening and at 5 o'clock in the morning we arrived to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1346"
					type="camp">Bentschen</placeName><note place="bottom">completed, not legible in original</note>. There we all had to get off, then
				we were examined for money, where several people had to go through <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120"
					type="subject">posts</term> next to each other. It was not examined however very exactly, I could e.g. keep several hundred Marks
				with me. Then a terrible march of about 7 kilometers began, without consideration of the physical abilities of the individual. If
				somebody could not carry his luggage or fell behind, the luggage was taken from him and thrown away. If somebody could not keep pace,
				he was beaten. Finally we reached the border. There is about 100 meters of no man’s land on both sides. On the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> side there was a single <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject">guard</term> with a rusted rifle. Nobody wanted to
				let him through. But the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germans</placeName> pushed
				from behind and pushed and said: <q>You won’t let a single man stop you!</q> Finally a few younger men formed a chain, went under the
				barrier and shouted to the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poles</placeName>: <q>Shoot us</q>.
				The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> side then shot into the air a few
				times, but since the crowd was pushing and the barrier was already raised, the whole procession finally reached <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> territory.</p>

			<p>7.) In the meantime, negotiations were going on there somehow and everyone first came to a little wood on the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> side, where they sat down tired to death, ate what
				they still had with them, and so on. From approx. 10 - 1 o'clock we were in the wood, in the pouring rain. Then the permission of the
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> government arrived to let us in to
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3080495/zbaszyn.html">Sbonczyn</placeName>. So we were able to leave again, and there were
				horde stables provided for us, which happened to be empty. We were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837"
					type="subject">accommodated</term> there, as good as it could be, and some people from other cities had already been there from
				the day before. The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3080494/zbaszynek.html">station Neu-Bentschen</placeName> was already
				black from people who had been there from the day before, the first 20 to 30 had been able to continue, but then the onward journey
				was generally blocked. At the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3080494/zbaszynek.html">station</placeName> there was no more
				space for anyone, because it was completely overcrowded. We spent the night in a horse stable, or more correctly, we started to spend
				the night there. My <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term> stayed on the
				ground floor, I and my two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughters</term> went up
				to the hayloft because it seemed warmer to us there. But afterwards other people lit lights there, and it became too flammable for us
				to go down again. Meanwhile my youngest <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
					>daughter</term> got very <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> and I went
				outside with both <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughters</term>. There, my older
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> also collapsed.</p>

			<pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-YV5245989_03.jpg"/>
			<p>- 3 -</p>

			<p>Then, in the pitch blackness, I groped my way further for some help and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">accommodation</term>. I heard voices and saw a light
				and finally found an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">inn</term>. I came into a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">room</term> smoked with tobacco in which there were
				many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-304" type="subject">refugees</term>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>, who were almost unconscious, were
				immediately put on two cane chairs and we got hot <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject"
					>coffee</term>. Here I was discovered by chance by an acquaintance from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2934691/duisburg.html">Duisburg</placeName>, who had got a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">room</term> in this <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">hotel</term> only yesterday. He said there was
				unfortunately no space in his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">room</term> because he
				had his two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> there and his <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">wife</term> was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term>. But there was another vacancy next to his
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">room</term>, because the owner had gone on a
				night’s journey. I replied - still in old ideas - that I could not stay in a strange <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">room</term>. But he said that that was not the point
				now. Then he opened the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">room</term> with a randomly
				matching key, and we found a wonderful <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">room</term>
				with a tiled stove, electric light, two large beds, etc., and so on. There I first put the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> in their beds, and then I went in
				search of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">milk</term>. Finally I found a farm and
				asked if I could get some <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">milk</term>. They even
				warmed it up for me, and I brought the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">milk</term>
				to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">inn</term>. When I came back, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> had already recovered to some
				extent.</p>

			<p>8.) The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">accommodation</term> was such that everyone
				had to put themselves in places and had to pay for them first. It was not a common <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-505" type="subject">camp</term>, but <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">accommodation</term> with <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">families</term> in the village, but the whole place
				was sealed off by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject">police</term> and none of us
				was allowed to leave it. Who had no money at all or in a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-505"
					type="subject">collection camp</term>, which was set up in two mills. On the second day, large lorries with <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> came from the Jewish places in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>, distributing <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">butter</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">eggs</term>. Gradually the whole thing was organized,
				committees were formed, delegates of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-317" type="subject"
					>organizations</term> came from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>, and the head was
				Prof. <persName ref="#ehri_et_ginsburg">Ginsburg</persName>. The committee then took over the payment of all rents, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">field kitchens</term> were set up, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothing</term> for the winter came, etc., etc. Of
				course it took a long time until the distribution was organized properly. We couldn’t stomach the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> from the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">field kitchen</term>, but since we still had some
				money, we were able to manage the necessities ourselves.</p>

			<p>9.) There were some young people together who belonged to the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004639"
					>Mizrahi</orgName>. Their meeting room was our room, the largest and brightest. They thought of writing to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-880" type="subject">Palestine Office</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName> and asking for <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-867" type="subject">certificates</term>. After some consideration they
				changed the plan and asked for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-867" type="subject">certificates</term>
				for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">parents</term>. We adults considered this
				attempt to be ridiculous. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">children</term>
				prepared 15 applications and sent them to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. Already
				after 3 days an emissary from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>, Dr. <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_wilhelm">Wilhelm</persName>, came and recorded more detailed personal data. And after a very short time we were
				informed by telephone that our <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-867" type="subject">certificate</term>
				had been approved. We don’t know why our <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-867" type="subject"
					>certificate</term> was granted, maybe it was connected to the fact that we were known from <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004639">Mizrahi work</orgName> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911298/hamburg.html">Hamburg</placeName>, maybe also with the fact that our eldest <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> was already in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6254930/palestine.html">Palestine</placeName> and that we had two <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> here.</p>

			<p>In total, however, only 5 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-867" type="subject">certificates</term> were
				given for the approximately 6500 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject">refugees</term> in
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1346" type="camp">Sbonczyn</placeName> at that time. We got one
				of them. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1141" type="subject">passports</term> were immediately
				taken from us, sent to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName> and so on. At the last moment it
				turned out that our older <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term>, because
				already over 18, could not come with us. So at first I didn’t want to travel, but I was forced at gunpoint and my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> demanded that we should travel, she
				herself would somehow get through. In fact, about 3 weeks later, she arrived with the so-called <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-912" type="subject">Aliya Bet</term>, on the first <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-301" type="subject">Greek ship</term> to dock in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/294117/nahariyya.html">Nahariyya</placeName>. We left <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3080495/zbaszyn.htmlv">Sbonczyn</placeName> on <date when="1938-12-22">December 22nd</date>, we
				didn’t have any money left at all, and the whole trip and equipment was paid for by the Jewish public authorities in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>. I received the cheque - 5000 zloty - myself.
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-301" type="subject">Ship Konstanca</term>
				<date when="1939-01-29">29 January</date>.</p>
		</body>
